Don’t leave this one at home this time of year… 

Amy’s Ant fishes best June through September.  To increase success rates, methodically cover water and show your fly to the most fish as possible.  We typically dead-drift Amy’s Ant most of the time but don’t be afraid to use it as an indicator and in a dry-dropper rig!

🔥Tungsten Breadcrust Jig 🔥
Whether you tie or buy, we have these flies and/or grouse fans available on our website! 

RECIPE: 

Hook: 12-18 TMC XC400BL
Bead: Tungsten Slotted, Gold
Thread: Brown Veevus 10/0
Underbody: Black or brown yarn
Abdomen: Red-phase ruffed-grouse quill
Collar: Grizzly Hen
